  "prompt": "Who create Quora?",
  "response": "Quora was co-founded by Adam D'Angelo and Charlie Cheever in June 2009. Both founders previously worked together at Facebook\u2014Adam D'Angelo served as Facebook's Chief Technology Officer before leaving to start Quora. The platform was created to provide a space where people could ask questions and collaboratively share knowledge and insights on a wide range of topics.\n\n**Founders:**\n\n1. **Adam D'Angelo**: Before founding Quora, Adam was the CTO at Facebook. He holds a degree in computer science from the California Institute of Technology (Caltech).\n\n2. **Charlie Cheever**: Charlie also worked at Facebook alongside Adam before co-founding Quora. He graduated from Harvard University with a degree in computer science.\n\nSince its inception, Quora has grown into a widely used knowledge-sharing platform, attracting millions of users worldwide who contribute by asking questions, providing answers, and engaging in discussions on diverse subjects.",
